race.comment: Competitive. BAKERSBEND (2) has been racing in stronger since the easy Maiden win. Raced a $4 favourite here last time and has the blinkers applied for the first time. Maps well and Yendall is a key jockey engagement. Suited and hits the race at peak. TURN UP THE NIGHT (17) finished ahead of the above in the same contest and has more up the sleeve. Has a handy gate and will strip fitter. FLITGROVE (6) resumes and brings three sharp jumpouts from Flemington. Has a low gate and Coffey aboard, and on what we have seen, she also has claims. OLIVIA'S SCANDAL (12) did a good job winning a country Maiden first up, as the market anticipated. This is a step-up, but expect her to be around the mark with the extra fitness.
